<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title>Responsive CSS Grid — Example</title>
  <style>
    /* Reset-ish */
    * { box-sizing: border-box; }
    body { font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial; margin: 0; padding: 24px; background: #f4f6f8; color: #111; }

    h1 { margin: 0 0 12px 0; font-size: 1.4rem; }
    p.lead { margin: 0 0 20px 0; color: #444; }

    /* Grid container */
    .grid-demo {
      display: grid;
      gap: 16px;                 /* space between grid cells */
      grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); /* 4 equal columns */
      grid-auto-rows: 120px;     /* default row height */
      align-items: center;       /* vertical alignment of items inside their cells */
      justify-items: stretch;    /* horizontal alignment of items inside their cells */
      padding: 16px;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #89f7fe, #66a6ff);
      border-radius: 12px;
      box-shadow: 0 6px 18px rgba(13,16,20,0.06);
    }

    /* Item styles */
    .card {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center; /* align content inside card */
      justify-content: center; /* center text horizontally */
      padding: 12px;
      border-radius: 8px;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #ff9a9e, #fad0c4);
      border: 1px solid rgba(20,24,30,0.06);
      font-weight: 600;
      color: #0b3a66;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba(11, 58, 102, 0.04);
    }

    /* Examples of spanning */
    .span-2 { grid-column: span 2; }
    .span-3 { grid-column: span 3; }
    .tall   { grid-row: span 2; }

    /* Centering examples */
    .centered { place-items: center; display: grid; }

    /* Utility: small text inside cell */
    .meta { font-size: 0.8rem; color: #43607a; font-weight: 500; }

    /* Responsive: collapse columns on smaller screens */
    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .grid-demo { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); }
    }
    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      .grid-demo { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); grid-auto-rows: 100px; }
    }
    @media (max-width: 420px) {
      .grid-demo { grid-template-columns: 1fr; grid-auto-rows: 90px; }
    }

    /* Small explanatory area */
    .legend { margin-top: 14px; color: #334a5e; font-size: 0.95rem; }
    .kbd { background:#eef6ff; border-radius:6px; padding:2px 6px; font-weight:700; font-size:0.85rem; }

  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Responsive CSS Grid — Example</h1>
  <p class="lead">A neat, practical grid using modern CSS Grid features: auto rows, spanning, alignment utilities and responsive breakpoints.</p>

  <section class="grid-demo" aria-label="Demo grid">
    <div class="card span-2">Header (span-2)</div>
    <div class="card">1</div>
    <div class="card">2</div>
    <div class="card tall">Sidebar (tall)</div>
    <div class="card">3</div>
    <div class="card span-3 centered">Featured (span-3, centered)<div style="font-size:0.75rem;margin-top:6px;" class="meta">Uses <span class="kbd">grid-column</span> & <span class="kbd">place-items</span></div></div>
    <div class="card">4</div>
    <div class="card">5</div>
    <div class="card">6</div>
    <div class="card span-2">Footer (span-2)</div>
  </section>

  <div class="legend">
    Quick notes: <br>
    • <strong>grid-template-columns</strong> controls columns. Try <code>repeat(auto-fit, minmax(180px, 1fr))</code> for auto-wrapping columns.<br>
    • <strong>gap</strong> replaces margins between items. <strong>place-items</strong> is shorthand for <em>align-items</em> + <em>justify-items</em>.
  </div>

</body>
